<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>Cassandra on MCP Toolbox for Databases</title><link>https://mcp-toolbox.dev/dev/integrations/cassandra/</link><description>Recent content in Cassandra on MCP Toolbox for Databases</description><generator>Hugo</generator><language>en-us</language><atom:link href="https://mcp-toolbox.dev/dev/integrations/cassandra/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>Cassandra Source</title><link>https://mcp-toolbox.dev/dev/integrations/cassandra/source/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://mcp-toolbox.dev/dev/integrations/cassandra/source/</guid><description>&lt;h2 id="about"&gt;About&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://cassandra.apache.org/"&gt;Apache Cassandra&lt;/a&gt; is a NoSQL distributed database. By design,
NoSQL databases are lightweight, open-source, non-relational, and largely
distributed. Counted among their strengths are horizontal scalability,
distributed architectures, and a flexible approach to schema definition.&lt;/p&gt;
